Mexico Stocks: Grupo Mexico Falls; Industrias Penoles Advances

-- B y   B r y a n   G i b e l
-- 
2011-07-25T17:31:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/mexico-stocks-grupo-mexico-falls-industrias-penoles-advances.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.4 percent to 35,597.23.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, declined 1.2 percent to 42.29 pesos. The company
said July 22 that it has been notified of a lawsuit by Grupo
Aeroportuario del Pacifico SAB, seeking an injunction to block
the mining company’s offer to buy shares of the airport group
known as GAP.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 2.5 percent to 526 pesos, its highest
price since it began trading in 1992. Silver futures for
September delivery rose 40.3 cents, or 1 percent, to $40.525 an
ounce on the Comex.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Gibel in New York at 
 bgibel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
